---
title: Queso Frito Rice with Grilling Cheese, Charred Poblanos, and Salsa Verde
description: We’re taking a cue here from Latin queso frito, or firm cheese cooked on the grill. Although it’s often served as an appetizer or eaten along with breakfast, we’re making it the main event here and serving it atop a bed of yellow rice with poblano pepper slices and an herb-based salsa. It deserves to be the main event, too—once you bite into all that salty, buttery deliciousness, you’ll understand why.
